The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

 Tehelka charges

 New Delhi, Dec. 27: News portal Tehelkas spy camera finally stung Jaya Jaitly (in picture) after the CBI today chargesheeted the former Samata Party chief and two others for allegedly taking bribes to influence then defence minister George Fernandes.

 Jaitly, Major General (retired) S.P. Murugai and Samata Party leader Gopal Pacherwal have been charged with criminal conspiracy and accepting bribe from the reporters who posed as arms dealers.

 Another accused, Surender Kumar Surekha, an industrialist from Kanpur, was spared as he had turned approver in the case registered against the four on December 6, 2004.

 The CBI alleged the reporters, who posed as representatives of a fictitious UK-based firm, sought assistance from Jaitly through Murugai and Surekha to get orders from the defence ministry.




